title: Live: Dutton dismisses claim he's seeking 'Trump-like' powers
text:
By political reporter Stephanie Anderson Updated February 09, 2017 08:50:35 Map: Australia 
Immigration Minister Peter Dutton has dismissed claims he is seeking "Trump-like" powers to review foreign visas, saying a new bill is "perfectly reasonable". 
Labor has criticised the Coalition, which wants to introduce a process to update health and security information for some long-term visa holders as part of its plan to trial a 10-year visa for Chinese nationals. 
Follow live.
